  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite being a forthcoming title with no current citations or online mentions, \"Architectures of Resistance\" by Leuven University Press is positioned within a landscape of commercial linkage through platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, hinting at potential public interest.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Architectures of Resistance\" is set to be published in 2024 by Leuven University Press, yet it already shows signs of potential impact through its strong commercial linkage. The work’s presence on commercial platforms like Amazon and Goodreads suggests that it may engage a wider audience beyond just academia, hinting at its relevance in public discourse.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although no citations, mentions, or community engagement have been recorded to date, the absence of existing metrics does not undermine the work's potential. The established credibility of Leuven University Press as a reputable publisher provides a solid foundation for future scholarly uptake.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">With an inferred strength of 0.9 attributed to commercial linkage, there lies an opportunity for the work to resonate with broader themes in societal contexts. This connection is vital as it reflects emerging discussions surrounding resistance in architectural practices, which may appeal to both scholars and practitioners alike.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The indications of policy sustainability, with a strength of 0.55, may also highlight the work's relevance in addressing Sustainable Development Goals. As it moves closer to publication, it will be significant to monitor its trajectory to understand how it may influence both academic discourse and community engagement in the field of architecture and resistance.</p>",
